### Implement UI Feedback for RxDB Sync Status (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/replication.html

Demonstrates how to use RxDB replication observables and synchronization methods to manage UI loading states based on sync status. It ensures a local flag 'last-in-sync' is updated after successful synchronization and uses this flag to conditionally show/hide a loading spinner, preventing application blocking due to sync delays.

```javascript
await myCollection.insertLocal('last-in-sync', { time: 0 }).catch(); // ensure flag exists
myReplicationState.active$.pipe(
    mergeMap(async() => {
        await myReplicationState.awaitInSync();
        await myCollection.upsertLocal('last-in-sync', { time: Date.now() })
    })
)// observe the flag and toggle loading spinner
await showLoadingSpinner();
const oneDay = 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24;
await firstValueFrom(
    myCollection.getLocal$('last-in-sync').pipe(
        filter(d => d.get('time') > (Date.now() - oneDay))
    )
);
await hideLoadingSpinner();
```

