### RxDB Peer-to-Peer Replication via WebRTC (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/firebase-realtime-database-alternative.md

This code sample demonstrates setting up peer-to-peer synchronization using RxDB's WebRTC replication plugin. It connects directly between devices without a central server, using a signaling server for initial connection establishment. Requires RxDB replication-webrtc plugin and specific WebRTC dependencies.

```typescript
import {
  replicateWebRTC,
  getConnectionHandlerSimplePeer
} from 'rxdb/plugins/replication-webrtc';

const webrtcPool = await replicateWebRTC({
  collection: db.tasks,
  topic: 'p2p-topic-123',
  connectionHandlerCreator: getConnectionHandlerSimplePeer({
    signalingServerUrl: 'wss://signaling.rxdb.info/',
    wrtc: require('node-datachannel/polyfill'),
    webSocketConstructor: require('ws').WebSocket
  })
});

webrtcPool.error$.subscribe((error) => {
  console.error('P2P error:', error);
});
```

